### SCIM Endpoint URL

Configure your IdP with this endpoint URL:

`https://{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}-{% if account_name_prefix | upper != "NONE" %}{{ account_name_prefix | lower }}_{% endif %}{% if org_account_name | upper != "NONE" %}{{ org_account_name | lower }}{% else %}{{ snowflake_org_name | lower }}{% endif %}.snowflakecomputing.com/scim/v2/`

### What Happens After Running the SQL

1. A SCIM provisioner role (`{{ scim_provisioner_role | upper }}`) will be created
2. A network policy for SCIM access will be created
3. The SCIM security integration will be created
4. A SCIM token will be generated - **copy this to your IdP configuration**

### Security Considerations

- The SCIM token is sensitive - store it securely in your IdP
- The network policy restricts SCIM access to only your IdP's IP addresses
- Users provisioned via SCIM will have `LOGIN_NAME` set to their IdP username
- Deprovisioning in the IdP will disable (not delete) users in Snowflake

### IdP Configuration Steps

{%- if identity_provider == "Okta" %}
**In Okta:**
1. Add the Snowflake application from the Okta Application Catalog
2. Configure SCIM provisioning in the app settings
3. Enter the SCIM endpoint URL and token from the SQL output
4. Enable provisioning features (Create, Update, Deactivate)
5. Assign users/groups to the Snowflake application

See: [SCIM with Okta](https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/scim-okta)
{%- elif identity_provider == "Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)" %}
**In Microsoft Entra ID:**
1. Add Snowflake from the Azure AD Enterprise Applications gallery
2. Configure automatic provisioning
3. Enter the SCIM endpoint URL and token from the SQL output
4. Test the connection and save
5. Assign users/groups to the Snowflake application

See: [SCIM with Azure AD](https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/scim-azure)
{%- else %}
**In your IdP:**
1. Configure a SCIM 2.0 application for Snowflake
2. Enter the SCIM endpoint URL from the SQL output
3. Configure bearer token authentication with the generated token
4. Map user attributes (email, first name, last name, etc.)
5. Enable provisioning and assign users

See: [SCIM with Generic IdP](https://docs.snowflake.com/en/user-guide/scim-generic)
{%- endif %}